medical_history.chief_complaint: Cardiac arrest with pulseless electrical activity.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Approximately two weeks before admission, the patient fractured her ankle. On the evening of admission, she reported chest pain and shortness of breath before collapsing. Initially found conscious by paramedics, she subsequently became unresponsive with episodes of pulselessness.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Past ankle fracture; recent evaluation for varicose veins with a negative ultrasound result. No other relevant medical conditions specified.
medical_history.family_history: Mother had a history of phlebitis.
medical_history.social_history: Works as an administrative assistant, never smoked or consumed alcohol, has three young children.
